text.tspan: Share of global primary energy consumption by source
Global primary energy consumption, disaggregated by source. Traditional biomass as an energy source is included
here. 'Other renewables' represents all renewable sources minus solar, wind, hydropower, traditional biomass and
modern biofuels (e.g. geothermal, wave and tidal).
Source: Energy Institute Statistical Review of World Energy (2023); Vaclav Smil (2017)
